00:48:14.355 --> 00:48:15.680
Okay, there you go.

00:48:16.520 --> 00:48:19.400
You made a foosball table out of chicken wire.

00:48:19.400 --> 00:48:22.600
Not foosball table, ping-pong.

00:48:23.360 --> 00:48:27.780
You got the net up there and it's chicken wire.

00:48:34.253 --> 00:48:34.427
I don't know.

00:48:36.465 --> 00:48:36.630
I try.

00:48:36.630 --> 00:48:39.580
Well, we love you all.

00:48:39.580 --> 00:48:40.705
Let's pray.

00:48:43.493 --> 00:48:43.627
All right.

00:48:43.627 --> 00:48:46.710
I'm sorry if I come across cranky.

00:48:46.710 --> 00:48:50.760
I don't want to always let my emotions fly.

00:48:50.760 --> 00:48:56.450
People, I try, like I said, in my transparency, even with people at the church.

00:48:56.450 --> 00:48:57.600
I'm probably too open.

00:48:57.600 --> 00:48:59.200
Maybe I am, maybe I'm not.

00:49:07.267 --> 00:49:15.000
I don't have any other pastors that do what we do and try to just really be real with y'all with our lives, with our problems, with stuff, and just try to be so real that you realize we're just people just like you are.

00:49:15.000 --> 00:49:20.400
There's so many people who try to treat us like celebrities.

00:49:20.400 --> 00:49:23.613
Oh man, I'm so over Hollywood church stuff.

00:49:33.035 --> 00:49:33.230
Don't you?

00:49:33.230 --> 00:49:36.640
God uses me and he'll use you.

00:49:36.640 --> 00:49:40.540
I'm going to be real with you.

00:49:40.540 --> 00:49:42.304
Brandon Biggs has issues.

00:49:45.600 --> 00:49:47.888
Yeah, you can ask my family, my mom and dad.

00:49:47.888 --> 00:49:49.040
Call them up.

00:49:49.040 --> 00:49:49.947
They'll tell you.

00:49:49.947 --> 00:49:52.495
They go, 'Hey, you know what?

00:49:52.495 --> 00:49:55.257
Brandon puts his clothes on just like you all do.

00:49:55.257 --> 00:49:59.695
' I just told the Lord, 'Yes.

00:49:59.695 --> 00:50:03.152
' I said, 'Yes, I'll clean your bathrooms.

00:50:03.152 --> 00:50:05.187
' I was a janitor for 15 years.

00:50:05.187 --> 00:50:06.484
I'll clean your toilets.

00:50:06.484 --> 00:50:09.765
I'm not a janitor anymore, but I remember it.

00:50:10.275 --> 00:50:12.360
I was the one that cleaned the airplane.

00:50:12.360 --> 00:50:14.747
I'm the one that cleaned the cars.

00:50:15.280 --> 00:50:20.290
I was the one that did all those things and cleaned carpets for big mega-ministries and did it all.

00:50:22.615 --> 00:50:25.240
I worked at parsonages for big ministries and did it all.

00:50:32.116 --> 00:50:32.384
I got to see people whenever nobody else was watching, and I learned a lot.

00:50:50.720 --> 00:50:50.876
But I'm going to tell you this: with all that I learned spiritually and how I've pressed in, I missed the mark so many times and I fall in His grace.

00:50:50.876 --> 00:50:51.656
'God, help me.

00:50:51.656 --> 00:50:51.812
Forgive me.

00:50:51.812 --> 00:50:52.124
I need you.

00:50:52.124 --> 00:50:53.630
I can't do this anymore.

00:50:53.630 --> 00:51:00.064
' It's like today and yesterday, the day before—so many days you wake up and you go, 'Is today the day that I quit this?

00:51:00.064 --> 00:51:04.950
' and keep praying with these people when you have threats against your life?

00:51:05.980 --> 00:51:11.160
You have these things and you go, 'Is this really what you want me to do?

00:51:11.160 --> 00:51:15.548
' And He said, 'Yes, I didn't tell you it'd be easy.

00:51:15.548 --> 00:51:19.827
I told you you would be persecuted and people would hate you.

00:51:19.827 --> 00:51:23.320
If the world loves you, Brandon, you're not doing it right.

00:51:23.320 --> 00:51:37.860
' I just didn't realize there would be so many brothers and sisters in the body of Christ in the church, waiting to cut your throat and be jealous of where God's brought you.

00:51:37.860 --> 00:51:41.104
And I didn't do any of this.

00:51:41.104 --> 00:51:42.380
I'm just being real.

00:51:42.380 --> 00:51:43.430
I just said yes.

00:51:43.430 --> 00:51:44.980
I started doing videos.

00:51:44.980 --> 00:51:46.720
I started praying with y'all.

00:51:46.720 --> 00:51:53.400
I see things of the Lord, and I've been doing this since I was 16 years old.

00:51:56.206 --> 00:51:56.765
You can ask my mom and dad.

00:51:56.765 --> 00:52:01.080
I've been doing this since I was 16 years old when I was demonically oppressed.

00:52:03.640 --> 00:52:04.047
I had eight demons.

00:52:04.047 --> 00:52:12.149
They tried to take me to the insane asylum as a young man.

00:52:12.149 --> 00:52:17.400
Mom and dad didn't know what to do with me.

00:52:17.400 --> 00:52:21.415
I physically tried to hurt my mother several times.

00:52:36.605 --> 00:52:36.860
I did a lot of things that I wasn't proud of, but Jesus set me free.

00:52:36.860 --> 00:52:38.347
Jesus set me free.

00:52:50.360 --> 00:52:50.616
And yeah, I still deal with things.

00:53:03.200 --> 00:53:03.720
I still wake up every day and deal with things and read my Bible and pray and deal with stuff.

00:53:03.720 --> 00:53:12.360
Brandon Biggs is a work in progress.

00:53:12.360 --> 00:53:22.347
But the Lord asked me, 'Will you help me?

00:53:22.347 --> 00:53:24.120
Will you do these things?

00:53:24.120 --> 00:53:26.230
' I say, 'Yes.

00:53:26.230 --> 00:53:29.960
' 'Will you give this money away?

00:53:29.960 --> 00:53:31.496
' 'Yes.

00:53:31.496 --> 00:53:34.440
' 'Will you help build this church?

00:53:34.440 --> 00:53:36.680
Will you help me do this?

00:53:36.680 --> 00:53:40.609
' And every single time, I've always said yes.

00:53:40.609 --> 00:53:44.989
I've never told Him no, even whenever my flesh didn't want to do it.

00:53:44.989 --> 00:53:55.305
We stayed at the rat shack house—800 square feet with a hole in the floor with mold all in it, to the point it made me sick and I coughed.

00:53:56.507 --> 00:53:56.742
You don't understand.

00:53:56.742 --> 00:53:59.520
We had bad mold in that home.

00:54:01.635 --> 00:54:01.820
It was bad.

00:54:01.820 --> 00:54:02.846
All five of us.

00:54:02.846 --> 00:54:10.551
All five of us breathing in that mold year in and year out because the floor was rotten.

00:54:10.551 --> 00:54:13.880
Do you have an old picture of that old house?

00:54:32.120 --> 00:54:32.320
I wanted to show them our old house right here.

00:54:38.120 --> 00:54:38.840
You can see that I lived right here for 20 years.

00:54:38.840 --> 00:54:40.600
Now you say, 'Well, that looks nice.

00:54:40.600 --> 00:54:44.540
' I did the best I had with what I had.

00:54:44.540 --> 00:54:45.457
Do you see it?

00:54:45.457 --> 00:54:45.834
Twenty years.

00:54:45.834 --> 00:54:47.600
My little girl shared a bedroom with me.

00:54:47.600 --> 00:54:53.304
She lived on the top bunk while Diana was on the bottom bunk for 20 years.

00:54:53.304 --> 00:55:01.420
Yeah, we were on the bottom and she was on the top because we didn't have enough rooms.

00:55:01.420 --> 00:55:03.120
That was the bed.

00:55:03.120 --> 00:55:05.244
That was the bunk bed.

00:55:05.244 --> 00:55:06.608
See the bunk bed?

00:55:06.608 --> 00:55:08.272
It took up the whole room.

00:55:08.272 --> 00:55:09.893
That's what we stayed on.

00:55:10.364 --> 00:55:15.969
My wife and I slept on the bottom and my little girl had the top.

00:55:15.969 --> 00:55:19.980
When I'm telling you stuff, I ain't making it up.

00:55:19.980 --> 00:55:24.480
The board on the ceiling was for my special needs daughter so she could swing.

00:55:24.480 --> 00:55:31.547
After we had our third child, we didn't have a place to put her, so we put her on top and she is on that board.

00:55:31.547 --> 00:55:36.349
But I'm going to tell you, God brought us a long way.

00:55:44.887 --> 00:55:45.133
He told us how to invest, He taught us how to do things, and we've been faithful with what He's told us to do.

00:55:45.133 --> 00:55:47.480
Show them the bathroom.

00:55:48.600 --> 00:55:52.040
When I tell you the floor's falling in, it was falling through.

00:55:52.040 --> 00:55:53.700
Right there.

00:55:53.700 --> 00:55:54.740
Show it.

00:55:54.740 --> 00:55:59.697
Look, I had to put makeshift boards on the floor because it fell through.

00:55:59.697 --> 00:56:00.476
That's poverty.

00:56:00.867 --> 00:56:01.844
We spent 20 years there.

00:56:02.794 --> 00:56:08.600
The floor fell through, so I had to put boards there because it was messed up, but I didn't have the money to fix it at the time.

00:56:08.600 --> 00:56:10.080
Diana was going through college.

00:56:10.080 --> 00:56:12.390
I want to show you where Jesus visited me.

00:56:20.427 --> 00:56:20.729
That right there.

00:56:20.729 --> 00:56:21.636
Jesus came.

00:56:27.663 --> 00:56:27.874
When I told you Jesus visited me that night, He visited me where that washing machine is.

00:56:27.874 --> 00:56:31.291
There's a dishwasher on the side there.

00:56:31.291 --> 00:56:35.080
That's where Jesus came and stood.

00:56:36.550 --> 00:56:46.280
And you see, I didn't cover the tile with the wood floor because it was special to me because the tile cracked where Jesus stood.

00:56:46.280 --> 00:56:52.474
And I stood there and I wept because He came and visited me.

00:56:52.474 --> 00:56:55.600
I was at that sink doing dishes right there.

00:56:56.240 --> 00:57:02.383
I put those shelves up because we had no place to put our groceries.

00:57:14.497 --> 00:57:14.800
And I stood in there and I did that year after year.

00:57:14.800 --> 00:57:19.200
So when I tell you I come from nothing, it's real.

00:57:28.632 --> 00:57:33.953
You say, 'Well, that looks nice compared to what I have.

00:57:33.953 --> 00:57:40.780
' Well, I did the best I could with what I had.

00:57:41.227 --> 00:57:43.290
I fixed it.

00:57:43.290 --> 00:57:48.350
I wasn't a good carpenter; you can tell the lights are even crooked.

00:57:52.800 --> 00:57:53.070
We painted the cabinets ourselves.

00:57:53.070 --> 00:58:00.477
I painted it.

00:58:10.280 --> 00:58:10.480
And so Diana started eBay there, and she started everything we have.

00:58:19.280 --> 00:58:19.444
And we worked our ears off and we saved back.

00:58:19.444 --> 00:58:24.380
We saved back some more because the Bible tells us, 'Owe no man anything but to love him.

00:58:24.380 --> 00:58:26.926
' Sorry, I'm tired tonight, y'all.

00:58:26.926 --> 00:58:27.867
You're done.

00:58:28.613 --> 00:58:29.987
I don't want to show him any more.

00:58:32.627 --> 00:58:32.973
It's embarrassing.

00:58:40.960 --> 00:58:43.000
You know, when you look at that, you go, 'My God, we're just transparent.

00:58:43.000 --> 00:58:44.870
' It's real.

00:58:44.870 --> 00:58:45.635
Twenty years.

00:58:45.635 --> 00:58:50.669
Oh, Jesus used to visit me in here.

00:59:03.000 --> 00:59:03.185
I used to sit in here on the floor.

00:59:06.849 --> 00:59:07.093
I want you to look at that.

00:59:07.093 --> 00:59:08.926
Just being real with you.

00:59:20.850 --> 00:59:21.175
You see, Jesus visited me in here.

00:59:21.175 --> 00:59:25.080
That's where I raised the dog from the dead.

00:59:25.080 --> 00:59:29.862
The dog was dead in the room.

00:59:39.440 --> 00:59:39.632
And I had my washing machine.

00:59:39.632 --> 00:59:47.850
There was an old cabinet behind there and I tore it out because I needed room.

00:59:47.850 --> 00:59:54.013
And so, I'm just being real with y'all, that's where Jesus raised the dog from the dead.

00:59:54.013 --> 00:59:56.670
Poverty.

00:59:56.680 --> 01:00:08.920
All three of our kids were born there.

01:00:18.120 --> 01:00:19.520
But Diana made it through college.

01:00:19.520 --> 01:00:24.440
And we got through it, didn't we?

01:00:24.440 --> 01:00:25.940
Making minimum wage.

01:00:25.940 --> 01:00:30.240
I made less than $17,000 a year after taxes.

01:00:31.770 --> 01:00:32.020
But God, but God.

01:00:32.020 --> 01:00:45.110
So people are going to hate whatever they want to do, but they don't know where you come from and what you sow to get there.

01:00:45.110 --> 01:00:48.880
God's always good and God is always faithful.

01:00:48.880 --> 01:01:06.674
But I'm trying to tell you, don't give up on your dreams because right now, like I said, I have seven channels and we minister to people all around the world on a day-to-day basis.

01:01:06.674 --> 01:01:09.848
It's not us; no, it's Him.

01:01:09.848 --> 01:01:12.573
We had over 225 salvations this last video.

01:01:12.573 --> 01:01:13.587
Isn't that wonderful?

01:01:13.587 --> 01:01:21.725
But when you listen to Him and you're faithful and you're a consistent tither—we tithed even when we didn't have it.

01:01:21.725 --> 01:01:25.760
We weren't doing what we wanted to; we were forced to tithe.

01:01:25.760 --> 01:01:32.192
We tithed even when we didn't want to because if we didn't tithe, they fired us.

01:01:32.192 --> 01:01:37.213
We tithed even off of what we had, and if you didn't tithe, they fired you.

01:01:37.213 --> 01:01:43.680
We didn't have enough to pay our bills after we tithed, and we did it for thirteen years.

01:01:56.953 --> 01:01:57.872
We tithed and tithed.

01:01:57.872 --> 01:02:04.942
When you're consistent with your tithe—because your boss forces you to tithe—we learned how to tithe.

01:02:14.805 --> 01:02:15.070
It's because of that we learned.

01:02:16.743 --> 01:02:17.600
And the Lord will bless your hands.

01:02:17.600 --> 01:02:21.760
That's why I try to tell you all that you have tithers' rights.

01:02:21.760 --> 01:02:32.011
I believe with all my heart that God will bless you in the city and in the field, coming in and going out.

01:02:32.011 --> 01:02:40.818
When you come from nothing, if you give Him your finances and you give and you sow regardless, He'll bring you out of nothing.

01:02:40.818 --> 01:02:42.000
He'll give you an idea.

01:02:55.200 --> 01:02:55.495
And it all started when Diana said, 'I'll go to college.

01:03:04.680 --> 01:03:05.045
I'll get my master's.

01:03:22.872 --> 01:03:23.280
It will take us through this.

01:03:23.280 --> 01:03:24.920
' And I thought she was never going to.

01:03:24.920 --> 01:03:31.280
She went to night school while I watched the kids.

01:03:31.280 --> 01:03:34.300
I cried myself to sleep.

01:03:34.300 --> 01:03:45.938
I remember every night I'd say, 'Lord, I don't know how I'm going to get all this done today: all the homework, all the essays I had to write.

01:03:45.938 --> 01:03:58.520
' Because she was working full-time and after she got off work, she would go to school until the wee hours in the morning and then come home and do her homework; some nights she'd get only two hours of sleep.

01:03:58.520 --> 01:04:00.853
She did that for years.

01:04:00.853 --> 01:04:12.680
Then she'd get up the next day and go to work all day long and do things for the church.

01:04:12.680 --> 01:04:22.060
Both of us—I watched the kids while she was going to school and we worked our butts off to get where we got.

01:04:22.060 --> 01:04:28.540
Finally, after eight years, I'll never forget when she said, 'Honey, I'm finished my last class.

01:04:28.540 --> 01:04:32.225
' She graduated, and when she graduated summa cum laude, she was top of her class.

01:04:32.225 --> 01:04:37.269
I looked at her and said, 'My God, it's really over.

01:04:37.269 --> 01:04:42.955
We don't have to do school all night and I can spend time with you and talk.

01:04:42.955 --> 01:04:50.147
' After eight years, I felt like I hardly knew her anymore because she did it all weekend long; she was doing full-time school.

01:04:50.147 --> 01:04:52.140
Megan's therapies and everything cost a lot.

01:04:52.140 --> 01:04:58.573
Well, that was me; I was doing that with all I had, watching her and taking her to things while you were doing school.

01:04:58.573 --> 01:05:01.252
I'd go by myself.

01:05:16.055 --> 01:05:16.260
But I always want to present this stuff to you—it's not a sob story; it's our story.

01:05:16.260 --> 01:05:24.298
Well, when I walked across that stage, I felt like He walked across it with me.

01:05:28.737 --> 01:05:30.067
I was like, 'He's the one that helped me get it.

01:05:30.067 --> 01:05:37.234
' The dean of ORU laid hands on her.

01:05:37.234 --> 01:05:56.400
I couldn't go in with her to her dinner because they were celebrating her because she got summa cum laude and she had to go in by herself because Megan was so bad at that time.

01:05:56.400 --> 01:06:00.645
I sat out in the car with Megan.

01:06:00.645 --> 01:06:03.420
Diana was pregnant—I didn't know it.

01:06:03.420 --> 01:06:07.160
Actually, you weren't pregnant yet.

01:06:07.160 --> 01:06:14.800
You walked in and the man said, 'I don't know who you are, but the Lord told me to give you a word.

01:06:14.800 --> 01:06:20.620
I'm supposed to lay hands on you.

01:06:20.620 --> 01:06:23.103
You're called to the nations.

01:06:23.103 --> 01:06:26.716
You're going to be a prophetic voice to the nations.

01:06:28.600 --> 01:06:35.604
You and your husband are going to walk in a great call in the end times and you're going to lead many to Jesus.

01:06:35.604 --> 01:06:46.040
' So he laid hands on her, and I remember sitting there when she came out and said, 'Brandon, I got a prophetic word from the dean.

01:06:46.040 --> 01:06:47.173
' I said, 'What?

01:06:47.173 --> 01:06:50.840
Oh, I wish I could have been there.

01:06:50.840 --> 01:06:54.269
' So she told me all about it.

01:07:05.497 --> 01:07:05.743
But I was sitting out with Megan in the car, and I was so excited that we got that prophetic word.

01:07:05.743 --> 01:07:11.720
It gave me hope because Megan was struggling at that time.

01:07:11.720 --> 01:07:15.920
She wouldn't wear clothes and she used to wear diapers all the time.

01:07:15.920 --> 01:07:20.950
She used to take her clothes off whenever she got in the car.

01:07:20.950 --> 01:07:27.680
She didn't like the texture—the way it felt on her.

01:07:30.425 --> 01:07:31.400
You guys have no idea; she's come so far.

01:07:31.400 --> 01:07:33.815
It's been little by little.

01:07:45.634 --> 01:07:46.560
We were so excited the day she started wearing clothes because the texture of the clothes on her skin made her freak out.

01:07:46.560 --> 01:07:47.909
It was bad.

01:07:47.909 --> 01:08:11.440
But just saying, every single thing you go through along the way—like we always try to talk to you a little bit before we pray—I want to give you hope that if God can take somebody that had nothing and do what He's done with me and with her, God can do it with anybody.

01:08:21.645 --> 01:08:22.020
You just have to be faithful in your giving.

01:08:33.811 --> 01:08:34.080
You have to be faithful in what God's called you to do.

01:08:34.080 --> 01:08:41.390
Be faithful to your church.

01:08:41.400 --> 01:08:45.120
Wherever you go to church, honor that pastor.

01:08:45.120 --> 01:08:46.586
Tithe there, give there.

01:08:46.586 --> 01:08:48.130
Bless them; help him.

01:08:49.245 --> 01:08:55.512
You say, 'Well, I'm only able to do this.

01:08:55.512 --> 01:09:11.720
' Well, I believe with all my heart that God stretches your dollar.

01:09:28.759 --> 01:09:29.733
I know because I lived it.

01:09:29.733 --> 01:09:43.820
We were on food stamps, but we made it.

01:09:43.820 --> 01:09:48.991
We made it through.

01:09:49.839 --> 01:10:18.680
And you get to the end of your whole journey and you have memories to tell of your faith journey.

01:10:18.680 --> 01:10:31.373
It's adventures in faith, journeys in faith.

01:10:31.373 --> 01:10:40.600
That's what Diana and I were.

01:10:40.600 --> 01:10:50.760
We lived a hard time with Megan.

01:10:56.760 --> 01:11:20.680
I know there's a lot of you that have lost children and you go, 'Brandon, what's your sob story?

01:11:38.360 --> 01:11:39.267
I lost my kid.

01:11:39.267 --> 01:11:43.800
My kid passed away.

01:12:29.520 --> 01:12:30.120
You still have your daughter.

01:12:30.120 --> 01:12:35.200
' It felt like a death to us every day.

01:12:39.040 --> 01:12:39.640
It felt like a death that wouldn't go away.

01:12:39.640 --> 01:12:52.663
If you lose a child, you bury them and you grieve them and you still have their memory.

01:12:52.663 --> 01:13:03.747
But whenever I woke up to the memory of my daughter never going to live a normal life, it was like facing death every single day in my heart, every birthday.

01:13:03.747 --> 01:13:09.067
I'm not trying to knock; I'm trying to tell you what I felt.

01:13:09.067 --> 01:13:15.507
I can't imagine losing a child, but it's what it felt like to me.

01:13:15.507 --> 01:13:17.046
She turns 21 next week.

01:13:17.046 --> 01:13:20.113
Her birthday is March 18th.

01:13:20.113 --> 01:13:22.720
I'm so thankful for her.

01:13:22.720 --> 01:13:24.512
She's a blessing.

01:13:24.960 --> 01:13:25.410
We love her.

01:13:25.410 --> 01:13:49.664
Megan has come a long way, but like I said, I try to give you hope because I know I speak to people that live in villages, people that live with barely anything in all parts of the world.

01:14:03.880 --> 01:14:04.060
And you say, 'Well, Brandon, you look like you got a lot.

01:14:04.060 --> 01:14:08.573
